Package robot_2_0

Class Position

  • java.lang.Object
    • robot_2_0.Position
  • public class Position
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents positions in a maze and provides methods for reaching adjacent positions. The getter methods getX() and getY() return integers representing coordinates in a two-dimensional grid with {0, 0} placed in the north-west corner if a coordinate is given by an ordered pair {x, y}. This is reflected in the methods for reaching adjacent positions. If the grid is 2x2 the north-east corner is {1, 0}, the south-east corner is {1, 1} and the south-west corner is {0, 1}. This class also overrides Object.equal() and Object.hashCode() to enable comparison between positions and to enable effective use in hash tables.
